            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>Milk is a nutrient-rich liquid food produced by the mammary glands of mammals. It is the primary source
                of nutrition for young mammals, including breastfed human infants before they are able to digest solid
                food. </p>
            <h3> Benifits of Drinking Milk </h3> <img src="milk.jpg" alt="milk">
            <p> It's packed with important nutrients like <b>Calcium, Phosphorus, B Vitamins, Potassium and Vitamin D
                </b>. Plus, it's an excellent source of protein. Drinking milk and dairy products may prevent
                osteoporosis and bone fractures and even help you maintain a healthy weight.</p>

